SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c01817357
Version: 1

HPSBMA02448 SSRT061231 rev.1 - HP Network Node Manager (NNM) Remote Console Running on Windows, Local Execution of Arbitrary Code, Denial of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2009-08-18
Last Updated: 2009-08-18

Potential Security Impact: Local execution of arbitrary code, Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential vulnerability has been identified with HP Network Node Manager (NNM) Remote Console running on Windows. The vulnerability could be exploited by a local user to execute arbitrary code or to create a Denial of Service (DoS).

References: CVE-2007-0819

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Network Node Manager (NNM) Remote Console 7.50, 7.51, 7.53 running on Windows

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2007-0819    (AV:L/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       7.2
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

Note: Remote consoles access NNM services and databases running on the management station through the NNM user interface running locally. For more information please refer to "HP Network Node Manager - Managing Your Network with HP OpenView Network Node Manager'" and "HP Network Node Manager - A Guide to Scalability and Distribution" available from http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/manuals

RESOLUTION

Due to the file permissions required, only trusted users should be given access to the system running HP Network Node Manager (NNM) Remote Console 7.5x. Consideration should be given to making the NNM Remote Console the sole function of the system. Web browsing should be avoided.

For alternatives to the use of NNM Remote Console please refer to "Allowing Others to View NNM from Many Computers" in the "HP Network Node Manager - Managing Your Network with HP OpenView Network Node Manager'" document available from http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/manuals

PRODUCT SPECIFIC INFORMATION
None

